<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1530] Optimize changed readers notification to only update what has changed rather than rebuild entire KV heap</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1530</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As discussed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1207&quot; title=&quot;Fix locking in memcache flush&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1207&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1207&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and to build on what was implemented in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1503&quot; title=&quot;hbase-1304 dropped updating list of store files on flush&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1503&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1503&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we should modify the existing KeyValueHeap in place by reusing any open scanners possible.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12428014">HBASE-1530</key>
            <summary>Optimize changed readers notification to only update what has changed rather than rebuild entire KV heap</summary>
